</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
Consumes the seeds of common agricultural weed species such as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Capsella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capsella bursa-pastoris" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bursa-pastoris">Capsella bursa-pastoris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Taraxacum officinale" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="officinale">Taraxacum officinale</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cirsium arvense" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvense">Cirsium arvense</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Petit, S." journalOrPublisher="Agronomy for Sustainable Development" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" pagination="309 - 317" title="Weeds in Agricultural Landscapes. A Review" volume="31" year="2011">Petit et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, it was rare (n = 1) and was only found in the olive grove in the heterogeneous area.
</paragraph>
